summary: This is a letter from Expedia, Inc. to an FBI Special Agent, responding to a subpoena dated January 27, 2020. Expedia states that after a diligent search, they were unable to locate any responsive records. The letter is signed by a paralegal.

persons.name: Special Agent FBI
persons.context: The recipient of the subpoena response letter from Expedia, Inc. The agent is addressed at 26 Federal Plaza, New York, NY.

persons.name: Maxwel
persons.context: The subject of the FBI's subpoena to Expedia, Inc. The letter references the matter concerning this individual.

persons.name: Michelle Velasquez
persons.context: The Expedia, Inc. paralegal who signed the response letter to the FBI, stating no responsive records were found.

connections.description: The FBI agent is investigating Maxwel, as evidenced by the subpoena issued to Expedia for records related to Maxwel.
Velasquez, on behalf of Expedia, is formally responding to the FBI agent's subpoena.

events.title: FBI Subpoena Issued to Expedia
events.description: The FBI issued a subpoena to Expedia, Inc. for records related to Maxwel.

events.title: Expedia's Subpoena Response
events.description: Expedia, Inc. sent a letter to the FBI stating that a diligent search found no responsive records related to the subpoena concerning Maxwel.

keyFacts: The FBI was actively investigating an individual named Maxwel as of January 2020, issuing a subpoena to Expedia for records.
Expedia, Inc. conducted a search in response to the subpoena but found no responsive records in their possession or control.
The document is a formal, written response from a corporate entity (Expedia) to a federal law enforcement subpoena, indicating a legal process was underway.
